Beginning December 1, 2007, and each year thereafter, a person that owns, leases, operates, or controls an affected facility shall submit to the Department, the Department of Natural Resources, and the Public Service Commission, a report that includes:
Emissions performance results related to compliance with the emissions requirements under § 2-1002 of this subtitle;
The number of pounds of oxides of nitrogen, sulfur dioxide, mercury, and carbon dioxide emitted during the previous calendar year from the affected facility;
A current compliance plan; and
Any other information requested by the Department.
